          </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
            
            The Federal Reserve kept interest rates steady at 4.25% to 4.50%, citing strong economic growth, low unemployment, and still-elevated inflation. It forecasts <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #6b705c; color: black;" href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-22-03-2025-h2-2-two-rate-cuts-later-in-the-year" target="_blank">two rate cuts later in the year</a> but lowered its 2025 GDP outlook to 1.7%. Inflation remains above target at 2.6%, and upcoming Trump-era tariffs could complicate future decisions.

          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">The Fed will slow its balance sheet reduction to support the economy without stoking inflation. Though the labor market shows signs of softening, it remains relatively strong. Ongoing trade uncertainty and stagflation fears contribute to market jitters and shape expectations for future policy moves.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
