            <strong>
              

🇹🇷 Turkey cuts interest rates
</strong>
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Turkey’s central bank cut its key interest rate from 45% to 42.5%, marking the <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #6b705c; color: black;" href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-22-03-2025-wn2-4-third-consecutive-rate-cut" target="_blank">third consecutive rate cut</a>, as annual inflation dipped below 40% for the first time in nearly two years. The move follows a gradual policy shift after President Erdogan appointed a new economic team in 2023. Initially, rates were raised to combat inflation.
</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Despite official inflation data showing improvement, independent economists suggest the actual rate may be higher. The bank stated it would adjust policy cautiously, warning that inflation expectations still pose risks to long-term disinflation.</p>
        </mj-text>
