            <strong>🇫🇷 OECD cuts EU GDP forecast</strong>
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
            The OECD has cut its <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #6b705c; color: black;" href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-22-03-2025-wn3-5-eurozone-gdp-growth-forecast" target="_blank">eurozone GDP growth forecast</a> for 2025 to 1.0%, down from 1.3%, citing weak investment, inflation, and rising geopolitical risks. Global growth was also revised down to 3.1%. Germany saw the sharpest downgrade, now expected to grow just 0.4%. Trade disruptions, especially US tariffs, impact sentiment and dampen recovery. 
            </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Inflation remains stubborn, particularly in services, while central banks are expected to ease rates gradually. The OECD urges global cooperation and structural reforms to counter economic fragmentation and boost productivity, warning that risks to growth and financial stability remain high.</p>
